# PR code review (AI agent)

Every pull request should receive an AI code review before merge.

## When to review

- After opening a PR or when the user asks to review a branch/PR.
- After pushing substantive fixes to an open PR (re-review the branch diff).

## How to review (Cursor Bugbot)

Launch exactly one `bugbot` subagent (`readonly: true`, `run_in_background: false`):

```text
Full Repository Path: <absolute repo path>
Diff: branch changes
Change Description: <only if diff computation fails>
Custom Instructions: <only if user gave specific review focus>
```

- Use `Diff: branch changes` against the repo default branch (`main`).
- Use `Diff: uncommitted changes` only when reviewing dirty working tree before the first commit.
- If the target is a specific PR, check out that PR’s head branch locally before launching Bugbot.

## Present findings

Summarize Bugbot output as a table:

| Severity | Location | Finding |
|----------|----------|---------|

Sort by severity (highest first). Do not auto-fix unless the user asks.

## PR readiness gate

A PR is **ready for human merge** when:

1. Linked issue is clear and `Closes #N` is in the PR body.
2. Bugbot review completed (note “no findings” or list open items).
3. Typecheck passes for TS changes.
4. Test plan in the PR is filled in.

If Bugbot reports high-severity issues, fix on the same branch, push, and re-run review.

## GitHub

- Prefer `gh issue create`, `gh pr create`, and `gh pr view` for issue/PR operations.
- Optional: enable [Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/docs/bugbot) on the repo for automated reviews on GitHub PRs in addition to local agent review.
